All of our preparations are complete; it is time to put this plan into action.  As you've guessed, the next Heartstone Shard is located in the cave southwest of here.  We've cleared the area outside the cave of Guardians, but we cannot be sure if our actions have alerted them of the Shard's location.  Go forth prepared for a fight, and bring back the Shard!
The second Shard!  Fitting this together with the one you already carry seems to suggest that Gardius broke it into four pieces.  Follow the path east from the city and continue your search.

A few months ago, these strange men appeared in the cave right over there.  I'm not sure why they've come here, but rumor exists that some of the creatures inside carry a mysterious stone.  I'm not sure what the stone does, but I'm very interested in studying it.  If you manage to find one, please bring it to me.  I'll pay you nicely for it.
Hmm.  This is quite an interesting stone.  Thank you for your efforts.  Please take this gold as a reward!
The shining stone still drips with blood.

The Merchants Guild holds a monopoly on trade, and the use that fact to drive prices through the roof.  Our goal is to disrupt their trade and one way to do so is to cut off their supply of rare goods.  To the northwest, a merchant supplier discovered a rare gem in the lake and plans to sell it to the Merchants.  Travel to the lake, slay the supplier and steal that gem!
Excellent work, Wizard.  Preventing the Merchants from accessing all of the goods is the best way to end their monopoly.

Our success relies on our ability to provide Tempor with goods.  One of our suppliers just discovered a sunken ship in the lake to the northwest and plans to sell his findings to us.  Unfortunately, the Mercenaries know of his discovery and are making plans to steal his treasure.  Go to the supplier and protect him agains their attacks.  I'll send some of our soldiers ahead of you to assist in the defense.
Excellent job protecting our supplier.  You have done a great service to us and the citizens of Tempor.

Due to the lack of natural resources, the south-central area of Tempor is largly unoccupied by either faction.  Only this camp, and the Phoenix camp to the northwest exist, and that presents an opportunity for us to hold this area exclusively.  While this part of our nation won't supply us with goods, it will provide a staging area for assaults.  Wipe out their camp, and claim this area in our name!
Excellent job, Axis.  Take this jewel as a mark of your service to our cause!.  Head north along the path and find us there.

Welcome to the south-central area of Tempor, Axis.  Because this area holds little resources, neither we nor the Guardians place many camps here.  In fact, there exists only one Guardian camp to the southeast.  If we were to kill everyone in that camp, this area would belong solely to the Phoenix and it would allow us to stage our assaults without their scouts seeing.  Are you up to the task?
Excellent job, Axis.  I will send word of your service to us.  Head north along the path and find us there.

Ahh, Axis - so glad to see you!  My young friend here is interested in learning our ways, and I cannot think of a better person to show him our skills.  Take Francis to the Magicians' camp north of here and slay the Hydromancers there.  Show him the fear our arrows bring.
As I suspected, Francis has agreed to join our forces and it is all because of your efforts.  You should consider becoming a recruiter.

Axis huh - I think I've heard of you. No matter - I can sense your growing power and I have an opportunity for you.  A group of steel-wielders have set up a small outpost southwest of here.  Take these magic lenses and put one in each of the corners of their base so we can track their moves.  Do so without losing your head and this fine wand will be your reward.
Not a bad job - as soon as they have time to charge the lenses will begin transmitting.  Here's the wand as promised - make good use of it.
These were obviously made by treehuggers.

There hasn't been granola at the market in days, and the only thing that seems to make sense is those Warder's that moved in southeast of here.  I bet they are making granola bars.  I'll tell you what, I just received this sword as a gift from one of our smiths, but I have no use for it.  If you go and steal the Warder's granola bars, I'll give you this sword in exchange.
Nom, nom, nom - told you it'd be worth it.  *Smiling with crumbs on his face*  Here, take this sword - it's quite a fine weapon.

When a hero emerges, word travels quickly.  Among other things, I've heard you are quite good at retrieving things.  The Mercenaries south of here - lumbering idiots that they are - may not realize it, but one of their swords contains a very valuable gem on the hilt.  Retrieve that sword and we may find other uses for you.
Well done!  Northeast of here you will find another gathering of Merchants.  Speak with them and as you do so show this secret hand sign - it will mark you a member in our cause.

Survival of the fittest - a good mantra. The Mercenaries faction is successful because we can spot opportunities.  Do you see the opportunity here - of course not - it's north of here. There is a huge demand for animal fur and we have a suitor that will pay well for as many as we can collect.  Problem is, the furs are stored inside of a caravan protected by a group of Honor Guards.  Kill the guards!
Nice work with the guards.  We've got agents slipping in tonight to steal the furs.  I wonder how many socks we'll be able to make from that...  Anyways, take one of these as a reward!

The first two Heartstone Shards you collected were hidden in caves.  That leads us and our enemies to suspect that the remaining Shards are likewise hidden.  In efforts to prevent us from discovering another Shard, the Guardians have placed a large force outside of the cave to the west.  Kindly remove them for us.  You will find aid from your Phoenix brothers when you arrive at the cave.
All cleared, you say?  Well done.  Take this gold and make your way northwest.  I'll have scouts look through the cave for clues about the Shards

As you know, the first two Heartstone Shards were hidden in caves.  That obviously makes us suspect the remaining ones will be also.  We've received word that the Phoenix is planning a recon mission into the cave northeast of here.  They cannot be allowed to complete that mission in the event that they find it before we do!  Go to the cave and kill any Phoenix members who tries to enter.
Nine men they sent?  That's almost two camps worth.  They must think the Shrd is there.  Hmm - head due north and find the Guardian camp there.  I will send a missive to the city.  Good work!
The gold reads, 'Jwj Dkslkzx DKS KCNs eSJcn.'

We have been successful in intercepting many of the Guardians' messages, but they are becoming more clever.  A double agent we have on the inside revealed to me that they would be sending messages engraved into gold coins.  Before we can move a large number of our forces, we have to be sure that they still don't know the location of the next Shard!  Go east and retrieve the decoy gold from their caravan.
Well done collecting this gold.  I'll get this to our decoders right away.  Please choose one of these as a reward.

The combined efforts of the Guardians are starting to pay off.  We have two of the Heartstone Shards and are close to discovering the location of another.  The Phoenix are reeling, and it is time to strike.  One of the most instrumental Phoenix leaders, Warmonger Slaten, resides in the camp directly to the west.  Make this a demoralizing loss for them then return to me.
Slaten's end was too long in coming - well done.  This loss for them will hurt their morale more than anything.

While we wait for our decoders to discover whether or not the Guardians are aware of the Shard location, your presence has been requested in the city.  Go southeast and seek out Lord Gigatron.  He is the commander of the Phoenix forces in this area and says he has a special task for you.
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.

Your service in the field to the Guardians has reached its peak.  What's left of the Phoenix camps here have retreated and gathered together.  We are unsure of their intentions, but that is not your concern as of now.  Your presence is requested by Commander Gavalar in the city to the southeast.  Make haste to him!
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.

The Guardians have taken to stalling our efforts in any way possible.  Our scouts have eliminated all possible locations for the Shard outside of the cave to the northwest, and it seems the Guardians know it.  To prevent us from obtaining a third piece of the Heartstone, they've mounded huge rocks preventing access to the cave.  I need you to take these explosives and open that entrance again!
The cave is opened again?!  Excellent work.  The time for us to act is upon us!
The handle of the rod is extremely hot.

We are certain that the next Heartstone Shard is located in the cave to the northwest, and the Phoenix have anticipated our move.  To block our efforts, their magic-users have constructed barriers preventing access to deeper parts of the cave.  Our wizards inform me that if you can obtain one of the rods used to create the barriers, we can reverse the effect.  Make haste to the cave and bring me one of those rods.
Excellent work - I'll have our wizards create a portal to the cave and start working on removing those barriers.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

By the time you reach the cave, our Wizards should have those barriers down.  Because they've blocked the path, I doubt you'll find any of Phoenix members beyond those walls.  However, they should be of little concern to you inside the cave.  Gardius will have the Shard defended extremely well.  Retrieve the next Heartstone Shard from the cave!
And two becomes three.  It would appear that there is only one Shard left.  We must hurry - take the path north from the city, then east.  Find our camps there.

The Merchants of Tempor claim that they are just like the common man, but how many commoners ride around in fancy caravans?  We tire of thier hypocracy.  Moments ago, one of the merchants passed by here heading east.  Little does he know that he has a faulty wheel on his cart and will soon break down.  Follow the path east, and when you find the broken down caravan, do Tempor a favor and end that greedy man's life!
It seems our friends in the cart-making business are paying off.  Well done!  You are almost ready for our final task - follow this path south across the river and seek us out there.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

With the entrance now open, there should be nothing preventing our access to the cave.  The next Heartstone Shard must be located deep within its walls.  Take caution when entering the cave - Gardius will have placed extensive defenses.  Find the Shard so that we can unite it with the others you've already found!
Fitting this Shard with the other two gives the appearance that we are missing only one more piece!  We are so close, Axis.  Keep up the work!

Boy am I glad to see you!  We're in quite a rough situation here.  One of our high merchants will be bringing his caravan of goods along the road to the north any moment now.  The problem is that a group of Mercenaries just made camp and will no doubt ambush that caravan.  I can't send these guards and risk leaving my wares unproctected.  Can you go north and clear those Sellblades off of the road?
*Deep breath* Thank you so much.  You saved us all a lot of money by clearing the road.  Please take this as a token of our appreciation.

My head is still ringing and I haven't slept in days!  Ever since those rust buckets started patrolling the path near here it's been impossible to sleep at night.  I tried to meditate and focus but I can't take it any longer.  Their camp is northeast of here.  I don't care what you do, just make the noises stop!
I was napping when you arrived - best sleep I have had in days.  *Yawns*  Here - take this - have you seen my blanky?

The Magicians west of here are polluting our water down steam with their nasty potions.  There is a refinery on the banks south of their camp that they use.  Hunt your way through their cloth and use these explosives to destroy that refinery.  We cannot continue with this polluted water!  Do this for us and this bow will be your reward.
We heard the boom from here!  In a couple of days the timber and magic will clear and the water will be safe again.  You have been a big help.  Take this weapon and use it well.

Those tree-hugging maroons just let a whole slew of snakes loose in an armory of ours - stole most of the steel too.  That sort of act cannot go unpunished...  We are fairly certain that the culprits originated from the Warder camp to the southeast.  Go there, kill everyone that you see, and teach them that the Blademasters of Tempor are not to be toyed with.!
A finer thing for our cause you have yet to do.  Take this blade - may it serve you as you have served us.
The family crest of High Merchant Bolivar.

For some time I did a pretty good trade in the walled city south of here.  When the skirmishes between the Guardians and Phoenix broke out we were quickly advised to leave, and in doing so I left my faimly crest buried in a safe zone.  Things have quieted down - go there and retrieve my crest.  Be careful, young one - I fear agents of the Mercenaries may be looking for my buried treasure too.
Thank you, Axis. Please take this gold as a reward for your efforts.  You have done many great things for our cause.

At last our final task to you is revealed.  You have been a friend, ally and companion in our struggles against the Mercenaries, and we have one last need of your skills.  To the southeast camps the Mercenaries finest soldiers.  In order for us to trade freely among the cities, we need you to remove the threat that they pose.  Kill them; and if more come, kill them too.  Slaying twenty should be plenty.
Our finest wares are yours to choose from.  Select any one that you would like.  You have the deepest thanks from all of us at the Merchant's Guild.  We will forever be in your debt.
This bag contains sever large gems.

The Merchants are hoarders - that is another of their weaknesses.  Our insiders in the Merchant's Guild notified me of a caravan north of here that contains a small fortune of extremely valuable gems. Burn the caravan and steal the gems - you will get your share.  Oh - and they may have some guards, but if you want to be a merc you're gonna' need some practice.
Ha - look at these gems.  I love the sound they make when they clink together.  Here's your share of the gold - well done, Axis.

The end is at hand!  Axis, you have truly become a brother in our struggle to end the corruption and greed of the Merchant's Guild, and we have now the opportunity to strike the killing blow.  Northwest of here, the Merchant's Guild houses their best and last line of defense, The Faceless Protectors.  If we can eliminate them, it would leave the Merchants helpless.  Go to their camp and kill twenty of them!
The Faceless Protectors are legendary wizards, you have done a great service to our lands in defeating that many.  Take one of these as a reward for your deeds.  You will always be a friend to us

Do you hear the Blade's Song?  It is the pulsing low rumble of peace that every Blademaster hears in his heart, and it has become harder to hear since those Mages moved in next us and started chanting all the time!  Hmm - I have a great idea - let's have a singing competition.  Head directly east and teach them the song of steel!
A fine Bladesman you have become, and a great service to our cause you have been.  When you are ready for your final test, speak with me again.

The Blade's Song calls you, young Warrior.  I can hear it crying forth from within you.  We have one final task for you, and it is all that stands before you are deserving to weild Tallendor.  Northeast of here lies the Warder's most skilled bowmen, the famous Arrowslingers.  Prove your skill and slay fifteen of these arrogant tree-huggers!

Your journey has been long in coming, and I can now present to you the sword that we hold most dear among us.  We welcome you into our ranks as a Blademaster.  Whatever you choose from here, represent us well!
This pristine uniform belonged to an Arrowslinger.

I know it goes without saying, but the Magicians are the greatest of the three class factions.  We alone possess the ability to wipe out both of our enemies, but what fun would that be.  We are Gods among ants.  Instead, I propose this - go northeast to the Warder camp and acquire a clean Warder uniform.  I'll tell you more when you return.  Be off now!
Ahh, well done.  Well done, indeed!  I bet it was difficult to find a Warder who did not soil himself at the sight of one such as you!

Among the Warders, patience is valued as one of the highest disciplines.  There are, however, limits to everything, and the Blademasters of this area have exhausted my patience.  They trample though our forests with no regard for the negative effects they cause; we will teach them to respect this land.  Take this poison and place it in their water supply barrels inside their camp southeast of here.
Excellent work.  Perhaps their dying breaths will be made reflecting on how ironic their deaths are.  Take this bow as payment for your efforts. May you use it well.

Word of the commotion you're causing between the Guardians and Phoenix is spreading quickly.  We don't partake in either of their endeavors, but have a slight interest since you are a magic wielder.  My fellow Magicians and I are curious if the hype about you is deserved.  To the northwest you will find a group of Warders.  I bet you can't kill them all...
Well, I'll admit that I bet against you.  For losing, I promised to give this wand to you.  Use it well, young Wizard.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

Everything is as prepared as it can be.  Though the Phoenix has grown desparate, the Black Council has still managed to raise an impressive army.  Without the Heartstone, we would be forced back into hiding and the land of Tempor would be plunged into another fruitless war.  Go to the cave, and do not return until you find the last Shard!

So you met Gardius? And he gave you the Shard - good.  I and the other commanders were responsible for staging his death.  He started giving us information on the Shards when he feared the Phoenix would find them.
The inside reads, 'Duty is heavier than a mountain.'

The arrogance of those Magicians is infuriating.  Not only do they set up camp right next to us, but we have reason to believe one of their Dedicated is responsible for our missing signet ring.  We have stayed our blades for too long against their disrespect.  Go west and kill them until you find the miserable whelp who took it!  Bring the ring back to me and you will be rewarded
This will have to undergo a heavy cleaning; I can smell the stench of their magic on it.  Well done, may this blade grant you victory against your enemies.

While we wage war against the Phoenix, our researchers work through the clues Gardius left behind to locate the Heartstone shards.  The problem is that the Phoenix is doing the same, and activity in their main command camp has increased, indicating they may have discovered another Shard.  Go north of here, and place this Listening Beacon outside of their tent - we must know the location of that Shard!
The beacon is place?  Good!  I'll have men placed to listen to their conversations around the clock.

We need to stall the Phoenix from moving on the Heartstone Shard until we can discover its location from them.  While we listen in on their plans, you should seek out Commander Phroste in the city to the northwest.  He's in charge of all Guardian troops in this area and will be able to instruct you from here on out.
Well met, Axis.  Our time is short, so let us get to work.

Time is short, Axis.  The Black Council are very clever, and will not look at your reclaimation of the Heartstone as all bad.  They may see it as doing them a favor in reuniting it, and I fear they may turn the army they gathered against us.  We must act before that happens.  Take the Shards to our Researcher here in the city - only he can reforge them.
Ahh, it does feel quite inspiring to be holding the Shards of the Legendary Heartstone.  I fear that in reforging them, it will cause many deaths...but how many will it save?

Final preparations are being made in the hunt for the last Shard.  The Guardians, clueless as always, have scouts surveying the area watching our movements.  One of these scouting parties is camped too close to the cave for our comfort - especially since we'll have important work there soon.  Go to the camp northwest of here and slay all of the Aeromancers you find there.  We need that area clear, soldier!
Ahh good, the area is secure and we can do our business in the cave without notice!  Well done, indeed.

And so the time has come.  Lord Captain Aerist, the highest ranking member of the Phoenix outside of the Black Council, has requested your presence.  Aerist serves as the voice of the council.  Steel yourself, Axis; not many ever get to meet the Lord Captain, let alone the members of the Black Council.  Make your way north to our city with haste!
*Nods at you*  Hail, Axis.  Welcome to our capital city, and the finest hour of the Phoenix.

We are one step away from reclaiming the last piece of what is rightfully ours.  We know that as soon as we move into the cave for the last Heartstone Shard, the Guardians will send messagers from their city to alert their forces - this cannot be allowed to happen.  What I need you to do is to place this trap along the road leading out of their city.  I've marked the spot on your map for you.
The trap is set and all of our hardwork is about to pay off.  Prepare yourself to execute the will of the Black Council.

We need to stall the Phoenix from moving on the Heartstone Shard until we can discover its location from them.  While we listen in on their plans, you should seek out Commander Phroste in the city to the northwest.  He's in charge of all Guardian troops in this area and will be able to instruct you from here on out.
Well met, Axis.  Our time is short, so let us get to work.

Our forces are poised to move the second that word is received in regards to the location of the Heartstone Shard.  In the meantime, we need to ensure the Phoenix attack force is as weak as possible.  Our scouts have discovered a moderate-sized Phoenix band gathering southeast of here, near a cave entrance.  We're unsure if the cave is related to the Shard, but those troops must be destroyed!
Excellent job, Axis.  Having those soldiers removed will prove vital for your next quest.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

While you were out killing Phoenix, I received word from Cano that the listening beacon revealed that the Phoenix believe the second Shard is located in the cave to the southwest.  That would certainly explain why they had troops gathering there.  Make haste and get the Heartstone Shard before the Phoenix does!
The second Shard!  Fitting this together with the one you already carry seems to suggest that Gardius broke it into four pieces.  Follow the path east from the city and continue your search.

Rumors from my superiors are that we've discovered where the next Shard is located.  I'm not one for hearsay, so I think it would be wise if you got it straight from the horse's mouth.  Head to the city northwest of here and find Lord Ezzunos - he'll be able to tell you what's going on.
Well met, Axis.  Our time is short, so let us get to work.

The Guardians are aware that we know the location of another Shard, and we know that they don't know where it is.  However, they've taken precautionary measures and spread soldiers across this area of Tempor in efforts to find where we move our forces.  Luckily for them, they've placed a group at the southwest of here at the exact location of the Shard.  We need to remove them before we move in mass.
The area is clear, you say?  Well then, it is time for us to act.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

All of our preparations are complete; it is time to put this plan into action.  As you've guessed, the next Heartstone Shard is located in the cave southwest of here.  We've cleared the area outside the cave of Guardians, but we cannot be sure if our actions have alerted them of the Shard's location.  Go forth prepared for a fight, and bring back the Shard!
The second Shard!  Fitting this together with the one you already carry seems to suggest that Gardius broke it into four pieces.  Follow the path east from the city and continue your search.
The shining stone still drips with blood.

The Merchants Guild holds a monopoly on trade, and the use that fact to drive prices through the roof.  Our goal is to disrupt their trade and one way to do so is to cut off their supply of rare goods.  To the northwest, a merchant supplier discovered a rare gem in the lake and plans to sell it to the Merchants.  Travel to the lake, slay the supplier and steal that gem!
Excellent work, Wizard.  Preventing the Merchants from accessing all of the goods is the best way to end their monopoly.

A few months ago, these strange men appeared in the cave right over there.  I'm not sure why they've come here, but rumor exists that some of the creatures inside carry a mysterious stone.  I'm not sure what the stone does, but I'm very interested in studying it.  If you manage to find one, please bring it to me.  I'll pay you nicely for it.
Hmm.  This is quite an interesting stone.  Thank you for your efforts.  Please take this gold as a reward!

Our success relies on our ability to provide Tempor with goods.  One of our suppliers just discovered a sunken ship in the lake to the northwest and plans to sell his findings to us.  Unfortunately, the Mercenaries know of his discovery and are making plans to steal his treasure.  Go to the supplier and protect him agains their attacks.  I'll send some of our soldiers ahead of you to assist in the defense.
Excellent job protecting our supplier.  You have done a great service to us and the citizens of Tempor.

Due to the lack of natural resources, the south-central area of Tempor is largly unoccupied by either faction.  Only this camp, and the Phoenix camp to the northwest exist, and that presents an opportunity for us to hold this area exclusively.  While this part of our nation won't supply us with goods, it will provide a staging area for assaults.  Wipe out their camp, and claim this area in our name!
Excellent job, Axis.  Take this jewel as a mark of your service to our cause!.  Head north along the path and find us there.

Welcome to the south-central area of Tempor, Axis.  Because this area holds little resources, neither we nor the Guardians place many camps here.  In fact, there exists only one Guardian camp to the southeast.  If we were to kill everyone in that camp, this area would belong solely to the Phoenix and it would allow us to stage our assaults without their scouts seeing.  Are you up to the task?
Excellent job, Axis.  I will send word of your service to us.  Head north along the path and find us there.

Welcome to Tempor, Axis. It seems our age of prosperity has come to an end as the Phoenix and the Guardians plunge us into a civil war.  The Phoenix is gathering an army for revenge against our enemies, and the Guardians are trying to stop them, claiming that another war isn't the answer.  Before thinking of choosing a side, head south and see my brother Skik.

This is one of Tempor's grand cities. Inside you'll find merchants, trainers, and a place to save your game.  When you're ready, follow this path east and prepare to choose a side in our civil war.  For information about the Phoenix and the Guardians and how they feel towards you, check your Factions Menu by pressing the 'F' Key.

It's time to act, young adventurer!  To the north lies the Guardians camp and to the south you will find the Phoenix.  Choose with which side you will ally, and make your way to their camp. When you arrive, seek out the quest giver, he will have a yellow symbol under his feet.  At any time, you can check your location on the Map by pressing the 'M' Key.

Woah there, adventurer.  The lands south of here are too dangerous for you right now.  I suggest you build your strength by completing quests in this area first.  Find your allies in the camps or in the city.  Gain their favor and become stronger before traveling south!

You'll find some dangerous stuff beyond this bridge, Axis.  Stuff that you aren't ready for.  Turn back and find the Heartstone shard in this area before you're ready to cross this bridge.  If you're lost, seek out the faction camps that you allied with.

There exists a third civil war in our lands - the war between the Mercenaries and the Merchant's Guild.  The Merchant's Guild promotes free trade and strives to provide goods to the cities of Tempor, while The Mercenaries fight to end the corruption and high prices forced on the citizens.  The side you choose will have its own rewards and consequences...

Beyond me you'll find some dangerous stuff, Axis.  You need some more training and experience before you're ready for that.  Find the Heartstone shard in this area first then you'll be ready.   If you're lost, seek out the faction camps that you allied with.

Greetings, Axis.  I am Brin Gardius.  Your surprise isn't unexpected; all of Tempor thinks me dead save for the few that know the truth.  But time doesn't afford us the luxury of small talk, the Black Council is about to strike and we are still drastically outnumbered.  Go to my things over there - you will find what you seek.  You must stop them!

Ahh, Axis - so glad to see you!  My young friend here is interested in learning our ways, and I cannot think of a better person to show him our skills.  Take Francis to the Magicians' camp north of here and slay the Hydromancers there.  Show him the fear our arrows bring.
As I suspected, Francis has agreed to join our forces and it is all because of your efforts.  You should consider becoming a recruiter.

Axis huh - I think I've heard of you. No matter - I can sense your growing power and I have an opportunity for you.  A group of steel-wielders have set up a small outpost southwest of here.  Take these magic lenses and put one in each of the corners of their base so we can track their moves.  Do so without losing your head and this fine wand will be your reward.
Not a bad job - as soon as they have time to charge the lenses will begin transmitting.  Here's the wand as promised - make good use of it.
These were obviously made by treehuggers.

There hasn't been granola at the market in days, and the only thing that seems to make sense is those Warder's that moved in southeast of here.  I bet they are making granola bars.  I'll tell you what, I just received this sword as a gift from one of our smiths, but I have no use for it.  If you go and steal the Warder's granola bars, I'll give you this sword in exchange.
Nom, nom, nom - told you it'd be worth it.  *Smiling with crumbs on his face*  Here, take this sword - it's quite a fine weapon.

The first two Heartstone Shards you collected were hidden in caves.  That leads us and our enemies to suspect that the remaining Shards are likewise hidden.  In efforts to prevent us from discovering another Shard, the Guardians have placed a large force outside of the cave to the west.  Kindly remove them for us.  You will find aid from your Phoenix brothers when you arrive at the cave.
All cleared, you say?  Well done.  Take this gold and make your way northwest.  I'll have scouts look through the cave for clues about the Shards
These were obviously made by treehuggers.

There hasn't been granola at the market in days, and the only thing that seems to make sense is those Warder's that moved in southeast of here.  I bet they are making granola bars.  I'll tell you what, I just received this sword as a gift from one of our smiths, but I have no use for it.  If you go and steal the Warder's granola bars, I'll give you this sword in exchange.
Nom, nom, nom - told you it'd be worth it.  *Smiling with crumbs on his face*  Here, take this sword - it's quite a fine weapon.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

The trap for the messager is in place and all other preparations have been made.  The time for our dominance is at hand.  Go forth, Axis - southwest of here to the cave.  Inside you will face whatever traps and trials Brin Gardius has placed in your way.  Defeat them and return to us with the final broken Shard of the Heartstone!  Failure is not an option.
What's this?  You say Brin is alive?!?  This is disturbing, but rather inconsequential.  With the power of the Heartstone, even he cannot stand in our way.
The gold reads, 'Jwj Dkslkzx DKS KCNs eSJcn.'

We have been successful in intercepting many of the Guardians' messages, but they are becoming more clever.  A double agent we have on the inside revealed to me that they would be sending messages engraved into gold coins.  Before we can move a large number of our forces, we have to be sure that they still don't know the location of the next Shard!  Go east and retrieve the decoy gold from their caravan.
Well done collecting this gold.  I'll get this to our decoders right away.  Please choose one of these as a reward.

While we wait for our decoders to discover whether or not the Guardians are aware of the Shard location, your presence has been requested in the city.  Go southeast and seek out Lord Gigatron.  He is the commander of the Phoenix forces in this area and says he has a special task for you.
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.

The combined efforts of the Guardians are starting to pay off.  We have two of the Heartstone Shards and are close to discovering the location of another.  The Phoenix are reeling, and it is time to strike.  One of the most instrumental Phoenix leaders, Warmonger Slaten, resides in the camp directly to the west.  Make this a demoralizing loss for them then return to me.
Slaten's end was too long in coming - well done.  This loss for them will hurt their morale more than anything.

Your service in the field to the Guardians has reached its peak.  What's left of the Phoenix camps here have retreated and gathered together.  We are unsure of their intentions, but that is not your concern as of now.  Your presence is requested by Commander Gavalar in the city to the southeast.  Make haste to him!
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.

As you know, the first two Heartstone Shards were hidden in caves.  That obviously makes us suspect the remaining ones will be also.  We've received word that the Phoenix is planning a recon mission into the cave northeast of here.  They cannot be allowed to complete that mission in the event that they find it before we do!  Go to the cave and kill any Phoenix members who tries to enter.
Nine men they sent?  That's almost two camps worth.  They must think the Shrd is there.  Hmm - head due north and find the Guardian camp there.  I will send a missive to the city.  Good work!

The pieces of the Heartstone are worthless unless combined, and few know the proper way to forge them together.  The news of Gardius' staged death has us all on edge.  He must have a plan for the Guardians, and we must make sure he isn't able to put it in motion.  Take the Shards of the Heartstone and travel to the river southwest of here.  Find Researcher Kykun and get him to forge them for you.
Wha? These can't be what I think they are... Tempor will have its vengence afterall!  Allow me a moment to forge these together for you.
Fool Me Twice, Shame on Me

I don't know how he managed to fool our assassins, but Gardius lives - our scouts have confirmed it.  He is a traitor and a theif, but most of all, he's a brilliant general and a deadly warrior.  If we are able to kill Gardius, it would shatter their faction and ensure our victory.  Brin has taken residence in an abandonded camp just north of the city.  End his life and become a hero to the people of Tempor!
The grand traitor is dead!  Victory for the Black Council.  Victory for the Phoenix.  Victory for Tempor.  Your name will go down in history, Axis.  Well done!

While we wait for our decoders to discover whether or not the Guardians are aware of the Shard location, your presence has been requested in the city.  Go southeast and seek out Lord Gigatron.  He is the commander of the Phoenix forces in this area and says he has a special task for you.
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.

The Guardians have taken to stalling our efforts in any way possible.  Our scouts have eliminated all possible locations for the Shard outside of the cave to the northwest, and it seems the Guardians know it.  To prevent us from obtaining a third piece of the Heartstone, they've mounded huge rocks preventing access to the cave.  I need you to take these explosives and open that entrance again!
The cave is opened again?!  Excellent work.  The time for us to act is upon us!
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

With the entrance now open, there should be nothing preventing our access to the cave.  The next Heartstone Shard must be located deep within its walls.  Take caution when entering the cave - Gardius will have placed extensive defenses.  Find the Shard so that we can unite it with the others you've already found!
Fitting this Shard with the other two gives the appearance that we are missing only one more piece!  We are so close, Axis.  Keep up the work!

Boy am I glad to see you!  We're in quite a rough situation here.  One of our high merchants will be bringing his caravan of goods along the road to the north any moment now.  The problem is that a group of Mercenaries just made camp and will no doubt ambush that caravan.  I can't send these guards and risk leaving my wares unproctected.  Can you go north and clear those Sellblades off of the road?
*Deep breath* Thank you so much.  You saved us all a lot of money by clearing the road.  Please take this as a token of our appreciation.

Your service in the field to the Guardians has reached its peak.  What's left of the Phoenix camps here have retreated and gathered together.  We are unsure of their intentions, but that is not your concern as of now.  Your presence is requested by Commander Gavalar in the city to the southeast.  Make haste to him!
Well met, Axis.  Thank you for answering my summons so quick.  We have much to discuss.
The handle of the rod is extremely hot.

We are certain that the next Heartstone Shard is located in the cave to the northwest, and the Phoenix have anticipated our move.  To block our efforts, their magic-users have constructed barriers preventing access to deeper parts of the cave.  Our wizards inform me that if you can obtain one of the rods used to create the barriers, we can reverse the effect.  Make haste to the cave and bring me one of those rods.
Excellent work - I'll have our wizards create a portal to the cave and start working on removing those barriers.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

By the time you reach the cave, our Wizards should have those barriers down.  Because they've blocked the path, I doubt you'll find any of Phoenix members beyond those walls.  However, they should be of little concern to you inside the cave.  Gardius will have the Shard defended extremely well.  Retrieve the next Heartstone Shard from the cave!
And two becomes three.  It would appear that there is only one Shard left.  We must hurry - take the path north from the city, then east.  Find our camps there.

My head is still ringing and I haven't slept in days!  Ever since those rust buckets started patrolling the path near here it's been impossible to sleep at night.  I tried to meditate and focus but I can't take it any longer.  Their camp is northeast of here.  I don't care what you do, just make the noises stop!
I was napping when you arrived - best sleep I have had in days.  *Yawns*  Here - take this - have you seen my blanky?

The Merchants of Tempor claim that they are just like the common man, but how many commoners ride around in fancy caravans?  We tire of thier hypocracy.  Moments ago, one of the merchants passed by here heading east.  Little does he know that he has a faulty wheel on his cart and will soon break down.  Follow the path east, and when you find the broken down caravan, do Tempor a favor and end that greedy man's life!
It seems our friends in the cart-making business are paying off.  Well done!  You are almost ready for our final task - follow this path south across the river and seek us out there.

At long last your epic quest comes to its final task.  Brin Gardius has revealed himself to Tempor and the Phoenix is stunned.  The Black Council has issue assassination decrees on both Gardius and you.  Brin has requested your immediate presence southeast of here near the Phoenix city.  Make haste to him and use the Heartstone wisely - its powers are not to be taken lightly.
The weight of Tempor rests on your shoulders, Axis.  It is good to see the Heartstone in our possession - we will certainly need it for our final task.

This is it, Axis.  All of our work - all of the struggles you went through - have led us here.  I know now that the Black Council is too corrupt to let live.  They must be removed from command, and you, with the Heartstone, is the only one powerful enough to attempt this feat.  I will send soldiers with you, but prepare yourself for the battle of your life - these Councilmen are not average politicians.
Victory for the Guardians, and victory for all of Tempor.  Your heroic actions have saved many lives.  You will forever be remembered as the hero of Tempor!

You now hold in your hands the single most powerful artifact that Tempor has ever known.  It is meant only for one purpse - destruction.  I'm sure the Black Council will make use of its power.  Travel back to the city quickly.
I can feel the power flowing from you.  Perhaps I could...nevermind...it is good that you have return so soon - we have need of you.

This is getting out of hand.  Ever since all of our local militia joined forces with either the Guardians or Phoenix, no one is left to fight off these wild wolves.  Without anyone to stop them, they've roamed into our lands and are killing our livestock and children.  I know you're mixed up in this civil war, but if you can spare a moment to kill ten or so, I would be very grateful!
Nice work - that should hold them off for a little, but we really need to get to the source of the problem.  I'll investigate!  Take this gold as a reward.

Hey there!  I don't suppose you've noticed the little wolf problem Tempor has stumbled upon, but they're everywhere!  The wolves in this area seem to be coming from a cave to the northwest.  If you get a chance, go into the cave there and verify that there are wolves inside.  No need to do anything else yet, just investigate for now.
Wolves in the cave, you say?  Interesting...it appears that we have some work to do.  Take this gold for your time.

The first thing that we need to do is to try and clear out that cave.  We can't have those rabid wolves running all over Tempor attacking and infecting people.  Let's do this - you go back to the cave and kill some of those wolves, and I'll look into the matter a little deeper.  Something seems a bit odd to be about this whole situation.
Nice work with the wolves.  I trust that a skilled fighter like yourself didn't have too much trouble with them.

Isis informed me of the help that you gave him near the city to the east.  With the Wolfmaster dead, I'm not sure why we're still seeing so many wolves around this area.  There's another cave directly south of the city here, but I'm not sure if that's where these Grizzled Wolves are coming from.  Go to the cave and kill some of the wolves there,  I'll check around and see if I can find anything out.
Nice job with the wolves - that should give us some breathing room around here.  It's just hard to go anywhere with wild wolves around.

While you were busy in the cave, I did some investigating of my own.  It appears that there is a deranged man behind our wolf problem.  He fancies himself a 'Wolf Master' and is living in the cave with the wolves.  If we want to halt the influx of wolves, we need to kill this self-proclaimed leader of the wolves.  I'm sure you'll find him deep in the cave
Excellent work, Axis.  You have done a great service to the citizens of Tempor.  Please take one of these as a reward for your efforts.

What's worse than having to deal with one deranged wolfmaster?  Having to deal with two.  It appears that the crazed beast-man that you killed had a brother, and he's taken residence in the cave where you just killed those wolves.  This certainly explains why the wolves haven't gone away.  You know what to do...
Dead? Good.  Now let's just hope that there wasn't a third brother.  I can't take anymore of these wild wolves.

If you thought dealing with wild wolves was bad - you're in for a shocker.  I'm not sure if you've run across these centaurs, but they're everywhere, and they won't hesitate to attack.  We need to reclaim our land and let them know that they roamed into the wrong country.  I've marked where some are on your map, but you'll find them other places too.  Kill fifteen then come back to me.
Great job - now maybe we can get back to harvesting our crops without fear of being attacked.  Take this gold for your time.

It appears that these wandering brutes aren't as dumb as we first thought.  While you were off thinning their numbers, a merchant came by here saying that he saw the centaur gathering around what looked like a clan cheif.  When they saw him, they ran to the cave in the northeast.  If we can kill this chief, maybe the centaurs will return from where they came.
Well done, Axis.  I really hope this ends our centaur problem here.  Please select from one of these items as a reward for your service.

Thank for your help with these young wolves - you were surprisingly helpful.  Say, if you're up for a harder challenge, there are some white wolves just south of here.  They're a bit more fierce than these younglings and have been an endless source of trouble for us.  Slay 5 of them then come back to me.
Excellent work, Wizard. We've really put a dent in the wild wolf population here.  Take this gold as a reward.

It appears that we have discovered the source of the wolf infestation in this area.  Apparently, there is a single wolf just north of the city that is breeding at an alarming rate.  By all reports, she is ferocious, rabid, and surrounded by her pups.  Approach her with caution and slay her!  If you can manage this, I'll reward you with a tamed wolf that you can ride around.
Fantastic work, Axis. As promised, here's your own rideable, tamed wolf.  Thank you for the service you have provided to the citizens of Tempor.

To say that we have a wolf problem is a drastic understatement.  If our nation had the resolve of these wolves, we wouldn't be in this silly civil war.  We've killed the wolf breeders, we've killed the wolf masters, but there are still more wolves... Go north east of here and kill the Dire Wolves that you find there.
Dead? Good.  Take this gold as a reward.

Ok - I promise that this is the last wolf quest that you'll get...Well, until Hands of War 3, at least.  Go north east again, just beyond where you killed the Dire Wolves, and you'll find the Pack Champion surrounded by other wolves.  Kill him, and the fastest tamed wolf we have will be yours as a mount!
Fantastic work, Axis. As promised, here's your new mount.  See you in Hand of War 3!

The Phoenix will stop at nothing to enslave our entire nation in a fruitless war. They've set up recruitment camps all over Tempor, and we need to put a stop to them.  Here's the plan - head south to the Phoenix camp and walk up to the table like you're going to enlist.  When you're at the table and have them distracted, we'll send in reinforcements.  Take out their entire camp!
Wow - excellent job! We could use a Wizard like yourself.  Go southwest of here and find the other Guardian camp for more quests.

The time for revenge is at hand! Soon we will punish our surrounding nations for their past deeds. Join our cause and prove your worth to me. To the north you will find a camp of Guardians who are trying to stop our recruiting. I do not want you to try convince them that we are right; I want you to kill them. You seem feeble, so I'll send some help ahead of you to their camp.
That took you long enough. I'll assume you were toying with them and that it didn't actually take you that long to kill them...

For months now, a group of wizards from The Magicians have been capturing our tamed wolves so that they would have testing subjects for their magic beard shampoo.  All forms of communication with them have been unsuccessful.  We need you to get rid of the wizards at the camp to the southeast of here.  Kill them all...
Well done, we weren't able to save all of the wolves, but we at least prevented any more cruel testing.  Take this bow as a reward!

Balefor sent you, did he?  He's always looking our for newcomers in the area making sure they understand the world they've entered.  I, on the other hand, try to prevent you from getting killed, and doing so requires your proficiency with that weapon you're holding.  I've created some basic illusions on the other side of this path on which you can pratice and perfect your skills.  Kill them then return to me.
Well done, Axis. Proceed along this path to the east for further instruction.

The Magicians west of here are polluting our water down steam with their nasty potions.  There is a refinery on the banks south of their camp that they use.  Hunt your way through their cloth and use these explosives to destroy that refinery.  We cannot continue with this polluted water!  Do this for us and this bow will be your reward.
We heard the boom from here!  In a couple of days the timber and magic will clear and the water will be safe again.  You have been a big help.  Take this weapon and use it well.
The family crest of High Merchant Bolivar.

For some time I did a pretty good trade in the walled city south of here.  When the skirmishes between the Guardians and Phoenix broke out we were quickly advised to leave, and in doing so I left my faimly crest buried in a safe zone.  Things have quieted down - go there and retrieve my crest.  Be careful, young one - I fear agents of the Mercenaries may be looking for my buried treasure too.
Thank you, Axis. Please take this gold as a reward for your efforts.  You have done many great things for our cause.

At last our final task to you is revealed.  You have been a friend, ally and companion in our struggles against the Mercenaries, and we have one last need of your skills.  To the southeast camps the Mercenaries finest soldiers.  In order for us to trade freely among the cities, we need you to remove the threat that they pose.  Kill them; and if more come, kill them too.  Slaying twenty should be plenty.
Our finest wares are yours to choose from.  Select any one that you would like.  You have the deepest thanks from all of us at the Merchant's Guild.  We will forever be in your debt.

Do you hear the Blade's Song?  It is the pulsing low rumble of peace that every Blademaster hears in his heart, and it has become harder to hear since those Mages moved in next us and started chanting all the time!  Hmm - I have a great idea - let's have a singing competition.  Head directly east and teach them the song of steel!
A fine Bladesman you have become, and a great service to our cause you have been.  When you are ready for your final test, speak with me again.

The Blade's Song calls you, young Warrior.  I can hear it crying forth from within you.  We have one final task for you, and it is all that stands before you are deserving to weild Tallendor.  Northeast of here lies the Warder's most skilled bowmen, the famous Arrowslingers.  Prove your skill and slay fifteen of these arrogant tree-huggers!

Your journey has been long in coming, and I can now present to you the sword that we hold most dear among us.  We welcome you into our ranks as a Blademaster.  Whatever you choose from here, represent us well!

You must admire the Guardians' commitment to their cause.  Despite their efforts, we have gathered three of the four Shards and are already looking for the last piece, yet they persist.  Directly east of here, they have set up camp to block our supply line to our capital city to the south.  The road is guarded by their Spellsparks.  Kindly remove them from our path, then return to me.
The road has been cleared, I trust?  Well done, Axis.  Make sure you visit the Phoenix camp to the southeast before crossing the river; they may have use of you there.

Each of the Guardian camps are designed to rival one of the Phoenix camps.  We will win the war by winning the small battles, but we are currently losing this one.  The Battle Clerics to the west have pounded our forces for days and we cannot last much longer.  Aid us here by going west and eliminating the threat of their attacks.  Remember this war will be won by winning the small fights.
Thank you, Wizard.  You have saved many lives here today.  Make sure you help the other Guardian camp to the southeast before crossing the river.
The contents of this book are written in a cypher.

Before the Black Council turned the Phoenix into a battle hungry machine, many of us, including Brin Gardius, served under their leadership.  Because of that, the Phoenix still has access to many of Brin's works and their researchers are sifting through them looking for clues about where he might have hid the Shards.  One of their researchers to the northeast seems to have made an important discovery - go steal it!
Excellent work - I'll send this to those who can interpret its meaning.  In the meantime head south accross the bridge and find out camps there.

This is going to be fun.  We know for certain that the Guardian Researcher southeast of here will be out of his camp for quite some time.  What you need to do is slip in and plant some false information among his readings.  This will lead the researcher to believe he's discovered something important and he'll pass it along to his superiors.  His 'discovery' will lead them in the wrong direction!
Well done, Axis.  This will buy us some time to make our next move.

The race for the last Heartstone Shard is underway, and the Phoenix are starting to panic.  What's disturbing to us is the length to which they will go to build up their army.  The Phoenix wizards have been tampering with dark arts and have resurrected fallen knights to reinforce their troops.  A group of these abominations exists to the west - kill ten of these Undead Knights then return to me.
We must capture the Heartstone before they take this war to another level.  Seek out the final camp southwest of here and discover your destiny!

When we make our move for the final Heartstone Shard, we must be certain that the Phoenix is too weak to interfere.  Their final camp in this area exists southeast of here at the edge of Tempor.  All of the orders for their troops are routed through there.  Take these explosives and burn it to the ground!
Next time, don't stand so close to the explosion; you're face is all covered in black ash!  Take this as a token of your bravery and service to us!

You and I knew it was only a matter of time before the High Lord of the Guardians made a request for your presence.  This is undoubtably in regards to the final Heartstone Shard.  Seek High Lord Axis inside the Guardian city just north of here.  Make us proud, Axis.
So you are the one of whom I have heard so much.  It is a pleasure to finally meet you.  My name is High Lord Axis, Captain Commander of the Guardian forces.
This bag contains sever large gems.

The Merchants are hoarders - that is another of their weaknesses.  Our insiders in the Merchant's Guild notified me of a caravan north of here that contains a small fortune of extremely valuable gems. Burn the caravan and steal the gems - you will get your share.  Oh - and they may have some guards, but if you want to be a merc you're gonna' need some practice.
Ha - look at these gems.  I love the sound they make when they clink together.  Here's your share of the gold - well done, Axis.

The end is at hand!  Axis, you have truly become a brother in our struggle to end the corruption and greed of the Merchant's Guild, and we have now the opportunity to strike the killing blow.  Northwest of here, the Merchant's Guild houses their best and last line of defense, The Faceless Protectors.  If we can eliminate them, it would leave the Merchants helpless.  Go to their camp and kill twenty of them!
The Faceless Protectors are legendary wizards, you have done a great service to our lands in defeating that many.  Take one of these as a reward for your deeds.  You will always be a friend to us
The leather is studded with pink gems...

This is rather embarassing...I was swimming the other day, and when I returned to gather my clothes, I discovered my belt was missing - not just missing - stolen!.  I followed the thief's sandal tracks to the Magician's camp southwest of here.  Nobody else knows this but I can't shoot straight without my belt - please get it back for me.
See how well it matches my boots?  I bought them together a few years back at a - heh - nevermind - take this as a token of thanks.

Many aspiring Rangers seek the training and discipline that we can offer, but few possess the skill to find homes here.  We extend training to many, but offer a place among us to very few.  I present to you a final task.  Southwest of here, the finest swordsmen in Tempor have destroyed the forest to make a camp for themselves.  Slay fifteen of them and take your place among the Warders!
It has been a pleasure to watch you grow into a fine Ranger.  I welcome you into our ranks as a fellow Warder.  Take this bow and become the legend you are destined to be.

Ok Axis, here's what we're going to do.  I needed that Warder uniform to cast an illusion spell on you.  Non-magic users will temporarily see you as a member of the Warders.  I want you to go west into the Blademasters' camp and wreck havok.  This will no doubt cause them to retaliate against the Warders!  Such fun this will be.  Do this and our greatest wand and a position among us will be your reward!
The only thing better than slaying your enemies is tricking your enemies into slaying themselves!  Well done, Axis. Welcome to the Magicians; may this wand serve your will

Brin Gardius, like all of the Guardians, were once members of the Phoenix.  We believe the work and writings that he left behind after his betrayal contain clues to the Shards, and our researchers have long searched for hidden meanings.  One researcher north of here is on the verge of discovering something remarkable, but faces threats from attacking Guardians.  Protect his life at all costs!
Excellent work protecting our researcher!  It will only e a short time until he finishes his work.  Head south across the bridge and find out camps there.
The leather is studded with pink gems...

I followed the thief's sandal tracks to the Magician's camp southwest of here.  Nobody else knows this but I can't shoot straight without my belt - please get it back for me.
See how well it matches my boots?  I bought them together a few years back at a - heh - nevermind - take this as a token of thanks.

Those tree-hugging maroons just let a whole slew of snakes loose in an armory of ours - stole most of the steel too.  That sort of act cannot go unpunished...  We are fairly certain that the culprits originated from the Warder camp to the southeast.  Go there, kill everyone that you see, and teach them that the Blademasters of Tempor are not to be toyed with.!
A finer thing for our cause you have yet to do.  Take this blade - may it serve you as you have served us.

Time is short, Axis.  The Black Council are very clever, and will not look at your reclaimation of the Heartstone as all bad.  They may see it as doing them a favor in reuniting it, and I fear they may turn the army they gathered against us.  We must act before that happens.  Take the Shards to our Researcher here in the city - only he can reforge them.
Ahh, it does feel quite inspiring to be holding the Shards of the Legendary Heartstone.  I fear that in reforging them, it will cause many deaths...but how many will it save?

At long last your epic quest comes to its final task.  Brin Gardius has revealed himself to Tempor and the Phoenix is stunned.  The Black Council has issue assassination decrees on both Gardius and you.  Brin has requested your immediate presence southeast of here near the Phoenix city.  Make haste to him and use the Heartstone wisely - its powers are not to be taken lightly.
The weight of Tempor rests on your shoulders, Axis.  It is good to see the Heartstone in our possession - we will certainly need it for our final task.
This pristine uniform belonged to an Arrowslinger.

I know it goes without saying, but the Magicians are the greatest of the three class factions.  We alone possess the ability to wipe out both of our enemies, but what fun would that be.  We are Gods among ants.  Instead, I propose this - go northeast to the Warder camp and acquire a clean Warder uniform.  I'll tell you more when you return.  Be off now!
Ahh, well done.  Well done, indeed!  I bet it was difficult to find a Warder who did not soil himself at the sight of one such as you!

So you are the one of whom I have heard so much.  It is a pleasure to finally meet you.  My name is High Lord Axis, Captain Commander of the Guardian forces.

Our scouts have strong reason to belive that the final Shard is located inside the cave to the south of here, but we know that the Phoenix is watching our movements.  Before I can send you for the Shard, we have to ensure that the Phoenix can't ambush you while you're inside.  Take these sentry wards and place them around the cave to the south, then return to me here.
Well done with the wards.  Please select from one of these in preparting for your final endeavor into a cave!
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

Everything is as prepared as it can be.  Though the Phoenix has grown desparate, the Black Council has still managed to raise an impressive army.  Without the Heartstone, we would be forced back into hiding and the land of Tempor would be plunged into another fruitless war.  Go to the cave, and do not return until you find the last Shard!

So you met Gardius? And he gave you the Shard - good.  I and the other commanders were responsible for staging his death.  He started giving us information on the Shards when he feared the Phoenix would find them.

Final preparations are being made in the hunt for the last Shard.  The Guardians, clueless as always, have scouts surveying the area watching our movements.  One of these scouting parties is camped too close to the cave for our comfort - especially since we'll have important work there soon.  Go to the camp northwest of here and slay all of the Aeromancers you find there.  We need that area clear, soldier!
Ahh good, the area is secure and we can do our business in the cave without notice!  Well done, indeed.

And so the time has come.  Lord Captain Aerist, the highest ranking member of the Phoenix outside of the Black Council, has requested your presence.  Aerist serves as the voice of the council.  Steel yourself, Axis; not many ever get to meet the Lord Captain, let alone the members of the Black Council.  Make your way north to our city with haste!
*Nods at you*  Hail, Axis.  Welcome to our capital city, and the finest hour of the Phoenix.

We are one step away from reclaiming the last piece of what is rightfully ours.  We know that as soon as we move into the cave for the last Heartstone Shard, the Guardians will send messagers from their city to alert their forces - this cannot be allowed to happen.  What I need you to do is to place this trap along the road leading out of their city.  I've marked the spot on your map for you.
The trap is set and all of our hardwork is about to pay off.  Prepare yourself to execute the will of the Black Council.
A broken shard of the legendary Heartstone.

The trap for the messager is in place and all other preparations have been made.  The time for our dominance is at hand.  Go forth, Axis - southwest of here to the cave.  Inside you will face whatever traps and trials Brin Gardius has placed in your way.  Defeat them and return to us with the final broken Shard of the Heartstone!  Failure is not an option.
What's this?  You say Brin is alive?!?  This is disturbing, but rather inconsequential.  With the power of the Heartstone, even he cannot stand in our way.

The pieces of the Heartstone are worthless unless combined, and few know the proper way to forge them together.  The news of Gardius' staged death has us all on edge.  He must have a plan for the Guardians, and we must make sure he isn't able to put it in motion.  Take the Shards of the Heartstone and travel to the river southwest of here.  Find Researcher Kykun and get him to forge them for you.
Wha? These can't be what I think they are... Tempor will have its vengence afterall!  Allow me a moment to forge these together for you.
Fool Me Twice, Shame on Me

I don't know how he managed to fool our assassins, but Gardius lives - our scouts have confirmed it.  He is a traitor and a theif, but most of all, he's a brilliant general and a deadly warrior.  If we are able to kill Gardius, it would shatter their faction and ensure our victory.  Brin has taken residence in an abandonded camp just north of the city.  End his life and become a hero to the people of Tempor!
The grand traitor is dead!  Victory for the Black Council.  Victory for the Phoenix.  Victory for Tempor.  Your name will go down in history, Axis.  Well done!

Make haste to him and use the Heartstone wisely - its powers are not to be taken lightly.
The weight of Tempor rests on your shoulders, Axis.  It is good to see the Heartstone in our possession - we will certainly need it for our final task.

This is it, Axis.  All of our work - all of the struggles you went through - have led us here.  I know now that the Black Council is too corrupt to let live.  They must be removed from command, and you, with the Heartstone, is the only one powerful enough to attempt this feat.  I will send soldiers with you, but prepare yourself for the battle of your life - these Councilmen are not average politicians.
Victory for the Guardians, and victory for all of Tempor.  Your heroic actions have saved many lives.  You will forever be remembered as the hero of Tempor!

You now hold in your hands the single most powerful artifact that Tempor has ever known.  It is meant only for one purpse - destruction.  I'm sure the Black Council will make use of its power.  Travel back to the city quickly.
I can feel the power flowing from you.  Perhaps I could...nevermind...it is good that you have return so soon - we have need of you.

This is getting out of hand.  Ever since all of our local militia joined forces with either the Guardians or Phoenix, no one is left to fight off these wild wolves.  Without anyone to stop them, they've roamed into our lands and are killing our livestock and children.  I know you're mixed up in this civil war, but if you can spare a moment to kill ten or so, I would be very grateful!
Nice work - that should hold them off for a little, but we really need to get to the source of the problem.  I'll investigate!  Take this gold as a reward.

Thank for your help with these young wolves - you were surprisingly helpful.  Say, if you're up for a harder challenge, there are some white wolves just south of here.  They're a bit more fierce than these younglings and have been an endless source of trouble for us.  Slay 5 of them then come back to me.
Excellent work, Wizard. We've really put a dent in the wild wolf population here.  Take this gold as a reward.

It appears that we have discovered the source of the wolf infestation in this area.  Apparently, there is a single wolf just north of the city that is breeding at an alarming rate.  By all reports, she is ferocious, rabid, and surrounded by her pups.  Approach her with caution and slay her!  If you can manage this, I'll reward you with a tamed wolf that you can ride around.
Fantastic work, Axis. As promised, here's your own rideable, tamed wolf.  Thank you for the service you have provided to the citizens of Tempor.

Hey there!  I don't suppose you've noticed the little wolf problem Tempor has stumbled upon, but they're everywhere!  The wolves in this area seem to be coming from a cave to the northwest.  If you get a chance, go into the cave there and verify that there are wolves inside.  No need to do anything else yet, just investigate for now.
Wolves in the cave, you say?  Interesting...it appears that we have some work to do.  Take this gold for your time.

The first thing that we need to do is to try and clear out that cave.  We can't have those rabid wolves running all over Tempor attacking and infecting people.  Let's do this - you go back to the cave and kill some of those wolves, and I'll look into the matter a little deeper.  Something seems a bit odd to be about this whole situation.
Nice work with the wolves.  I trust that a skilled fighter like yourself didn't have too much trouble with them.

While you were busy in the cave, I did some investigating of my own.  It appears that there is a deranged man behind our wolf problem.  He fancies himself a 'Wolf Master' and is living in the cave with the wolves.  If we want to halt the influx of wolves, we need to kill this self-proclaimed leader of the wolves.  I'm sure you'll find him deep in the cave
Excellent work, Axis.  You have done a great service to the citizens of Tempor.  Please take one of these as a reward for your efforts.

Isis informed me of the help that you gave him near the city to the east.  With the Wolfmaster dead, I'm not sure why we're still seeing so many wolves around this area.  There's another cave directly south of the city here, but I'm not sure if that's where these Grizzled Wolves are coming from.  Go to the cave and kill some of the wolves there,  I'll check around and see if I can find anything out.
Nice job with the wolves - that should give us some breathing room around here.  It's just hard to go anywhere with wild wolves around.

What's worse than having to deal with one deranged wolfmaster?  Having to deal with two.  It appears that the crazed beast-man that you killed had a brother, and he's taken residence in the cave where you just killed those wolves.  This certainly explains why the wolves haven't gone away.  You know what to do...
Dead? Good.  Now let's just hope that there wasn't a third brother.  I can't take anymore of these wild wolves.

Well done, Axis.  This will buy us some time to make our next move.

If you thought dealing with wild wolves was bad - you're in for a shocker.  I'm not sure if you've run across these centaurs, but they're everywhere, and they won't hesitate to attack.  We need to reclaim our land and let them know that they roamed into the wrong country.  I've marked where some are on your map, but you'll find them other places too.  Kill fifteen then come back to me.
Great job - now maybe we can get back to harvesting our crops without fear of being attacked.  Take this gold for your time.

It appears that these wandering brutes aren't as dumb as we first thought.  While you were off thinning their numbers, a merchant came by here saying that he saw the centaur gathering around what looked like a clan cheif.  When they saw him, they ran to the cave in the northeast.  If we can kill this chief, maybe the centaurs will return from where they came.
Well done, Axis.  I really hope this ends our centaur problem here.  Please select from one of these items as a reward for your service.

To say that we have a wolf problem is a drastic understatement.  If our nation had the resolve of these wolves, we wouldn't be in this silly civil war.  We've killed the wolf breeders, we've killed the wolf masters, but there are still more wolves... Go north east of here and kill the Dire Wolves that you find there.
Dead? Good.  Take this gold as a reward.

Ok - I promise that this is the last wolf quest that you'll get...Well, until Hands of War 3, at least.  Go north east again, just beyond where you killed the Dire Wolves, and you'll find the Pack Champion surrounded by other wolves.  Kill him, and the fastest tamed wolf we have will be yours as a mount!
Fantastic work, Axis. As promised, here's your new mount.  See you in Hand of War 3!

The race for the last Heartstone Shard is underway, and the Phoenix are starting to panic.  What's disturbing to us is the length to which they will go to build up their army.  The Phoenix wizards have been tampering with dark arts and have resurrected fallen knights to reinforce their troops.  A group of these abominations exists to the west - kill ten of these Undead Knights then return to me.
We must capture the Heartstone before they take this war to another level.  Seek out the final camp southwest of here and discover your destiny!

When we make our move for the final Heartstone Shard, we must be certain that the Phoenix is too weak to interfere.  Their final camp in this area exists southeast of here at the edge of Tempor.  All of the orders for their troops are routed through there.  Take these explosives and burn it to the ground!
Next time, don't stand so close to the explosion; you're face is all covered in black ash!  Take this as a token of your bravery and service to us!
